event.logging

Class SystemDetail

  • java.lang.Object
    • event.logging.SystemDetail

  • public class SystemDetail
extends java.lang.Object
    Describes the system that generated the event. This is not the same as the generator as the generator is merely the application or component that created the event, e.g. auditd. The system describes the higher level project/service or capability that uses the generator as a component, e.g. 'Payroll System'.

An instance may also be site specific e.g. a deployment at a particular data center. The way an environment is described will differ depending on the system and the way it is deployed however a good example would be REF_DC1 to indicate that the environment is a reference deployment in data center 1.
